---
import GuideLayout from "../../layouts/GuideLayout.astro";
import { uaeCostOfLiving } from "../../data/uae/cost-of-living";
import { buildBreadcrumbs, buildArticleSchema, buildFAQSchema } from "../../lib/seo";
import RelatedLinks from "../../components/ui/RelatedLinks.astro";
import SourcesBlock from "../../components/ui/SourcesBlock.astro";
import FAQAccordion from "../../components/ui/FAQAccordion.astro";
import CostOfLivingSimulator from "../../components/calculators/CostOfLivingSimulator";

const faqs = [
  { question: "How much does a single expat need to live in Dubai in 2026?", answer: "A single expat in Dubai needs approximately AED 8,000-12,000 (~€2,000-3,000) per month for a comfortable lifestyle. This breaks down to: studio/1-bed apartment AED 4,000-7,000 (~€1,000-1,750), groceries AED 1,000-1,500 (~€250-375), transport AED 500-1,000 (~€125-250), dining out AED 800-1,500 (~€200-375), utilities and internet AED 500-800 (~€125-200), and miscellaneous AED 500-1,000 (~€125-250). Higher earners in premium areas like Dubai Marina or Downtown can spend AED 15,000+ (~€3,750+) monthly." },
  { question: "Is Abu Dhabi cheaper than Dubai for expats?", answer: "Yes, Abu Dhabi is typically 10-20% cheaper than Dubai for most expenses. Rents are the biggest difference: a one-bedroom apartment in Abu Dhabi costs AED 4,000-7,000 (~€1,000-1,750) versus AED 5,000-10,000 (~€1,250-2,500) in Dubai. Groceries, dining, and transport are comparable. Abu Dhabi also offers more spacious accommodation for the same budget." },
  { question: "What is the average rent in Dubai for a family apartment in 2026?", answer: "A two-bedroom family apartment in Dubai costs AED 8,000-16,000 (~€2,000-4,000) per month depending on location. Popular family areas include Arabian Ranches (AED 10,000-15,000 (~€2,500-3,750)), JVC (AED 7,000-10,000 (~€1,750-2,500)), and Mirdif (AED 6,000-9,000 (~€1,500-2,250)). Family villas in gated communities range from AED 12,000-25,000 (~€3,000-6,250) monthly." },
  { question: "How much do international school fees cost in the UAE?", answer: "International school fees in the UAE range from AED 15,000 (~€3,750) to AED 100,000+ (~€25,000+) per year. Budget schools offering Indian CBSE/ICSE curricula charge AED 15,000-25,000 (~€3,750-6,250). Mid-tier British and American curriculum schools cost AED 30,000-55,000 (~€7,500-13,750). Premium schools like GEMS Wellington and Dubai College charge AED 55,000-100,000 (~€13,750-25,000). KHDA regulates fee increases in Dubai." },
  { question: "Do UAE expats pay VAT on everyday purchases?", answer: "Yes. The UAE introduced 5% VAT in January 2018, which applies to most goods and services including groceries, dining, electronics, and entertainment. Essential food items, healthcare, and education are either zero-rated or exempt. Rent is VAT-exempt for residential properties. The 5% rate is significantly lower than VAT in Saudi Arabia (15%) and there is no VAT in Qatar." },
];

const breadcrumbs = [{ name: "Home", url: "https://arabiaexpat.com/" }, { name: "UAE", url: "https://arabiaexpat.com/uae/guide/" }, { name: "Cost of Living", url: "https://arabiaexpat.com/uae/cost-of-living/" }];
---
<GuideLayout title="UAE Cost of Living 2026: Dubai and Abu Dhabi Prices" description="Detailed UAE cost of living guide for 2026. Rent, food, transport, healthcare, education, and utility prices in Dubai and Abu Dhabi with AED and USD figures." canonical="/uae/cost-of-living/" schemas={[buildBreadcrumbs(breadcrumbs), buildArticleSchema("UAE Cost of Living 2026: Dubai and Abu Dhabi Prices", "Detailed UAE cost of living guide for 2026.", "https://arabiaexpat.com/uae/cost-of-living/", "2025-01-15", "2026-06-01"), buildFAQSchema(faqs)]} breadcrumbs={[{ name: "Home", url: "/" }, { name: "UAE", url: "/uae/guide/" }, { name: "Cost of Living", url: "/uae/cost-of-living/" }]}>
<h1>UAE Cost of Living in 2026: Dubai and Abu Dhabi</h1>

<div class="not-prose mb-8">
<CostOfLivingSimulator client:load defaultCity="dubai" />
</div>
<p>Understanding the cost of living in the UAE is essential for evaluating job offers and planning your finances. While the absence of income tax boosts take-home pay, living costs in major UAE cities are comparable to premium Western cities. Dubai is generally more expensive than Abu Dhabi, particularly for housing and entertainment. This guide provides detailed price ranges for housing, food, transport, healthcare, education, and utilities in both cities, based on 2026 market data.</p>

<p>The UAE applies a 5% Value Added Tax on most goods and services, introduced in January 2018. Residential rent, basic healthcare, and local public transport are either VAT-exempt or zero-rated. For a single professional, monthly living expenses in Dubai typically run AED 8,000-12,000 (~€2,000-3,000), while a family of four should budget AED 18,000-30,000 (~€4,500-7,500) depending on housing and school choices. In Abu Dhabi, these figures drop by 10-20% for comparable lifestyles. Rent is typically paid in 1-4 post-dated checks per year, though monthly payment options are increasingly available through platforms like Keyper and other proptech services.</p>

{uaeCostOfLiving.cities.map((city) => (
<>
<h2>{city.name} Cost Breakdown</h2>
<h3>Housing</h3>
<div class="not-prose overflow-x-auto mb-4">
<table class="w-full text-sm"><thead><tr class="bg-teal-600 text-white"><th class="px-3 py-2 text-left rounded-tl-lg">Type</th><th class="px-3 py-2 text-right">Min (AED)</th><th class="px-3 py-2 text-right">Max (AED)</th><th class="px-3 py-2 text-right">EUR Equiv.</th><th class="px-3 py-2 text-right rounded-tr-lg">USD Equiv.</th></tr></thead>
<tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100 dark:divide-gray-800">
<tr><td class="px-3 py-2">Studio Apartment</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-right tabular-nums">{city.housing.studioApartment.min.toLocaleString()}</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-right tabular-nums">{city.housing.studioApartment.max.toLocaleString()}</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-right tabular-nums">€{Math.round(city.housing.studioApartment.min * 0.25).toLocaleString()}-{Math.round(city.housing.studioApartment.max * 0.25).toLocaleString()}</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-right tabular-nums">${Math.round(city.housing.studioApartment.min / 3.67).toLocaleString()}-${Math.round(city.housing.studioApartment.max / 3.67).toLocaleString()}</td></tr>
<tr><td class="px-3 py-2">1 Bedroom</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-right tabular-nums">{city.housing.oneBedroom.min.toLocaleString()}</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-right tabular-nums">{city.housing.oneBedroom.max.toLocaleString()}</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-right tabular-nums">€{Math.round(city.housing.oneBedroom.min * 0.25).toLocaleString()}-{Math.round(city.housing.oneBedroom.max * 0.25).toLocaleString()}</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-right tabular-nums">${Math.round(city.housing.oneBedroom.min / 3.67).toLocaleString()}-${Math.round(city.housing.oneBedroom.max / 3.67).toLocaleString()}</td></tr>
<tr><td class="px-3 py-2">2 Bedroom</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-right tabular-nums">{city.housing.twoBedroom.min.toLocaleString()}</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-right tabular-nums">{city.housing.twoBedroom.max.toLocaleString()}</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-right tabular-nums">€{Math.round(city.housing.twoBedroom.min * 0.25).toLocaleString()}-{Math.round(city.housing.twoBedroom.max * 0.25).toLocaleString()}</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-right tabular-nums">${Math.round(city.housing.twoBedroom.min / 3.67).toLocaleString()}-${Math.round(city.housing.twoBedroom.max / 3.67).toLocaleString()}</td></tr>
<tr><td class="px-3 py-2">Family Villa</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-right tabular-nums">{city.housing.familyVilla.min.toLocaleString()}</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-right tabular-nums">{city.housing.familyVilla.max.toLocaleString()}</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-right tabular-nums">€{Math.round(city.housing.familyVilla.min * 0.25).toLocaleString()}-{Math.round(city.housing.familyVilla.max * 0.25).toLocaleString()}</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-right tabular-nums">${Math.round(city.housing.familyVilla.min / 3.67).toLocaleString()}-${Math.round(city.housing.familyVilla.max / 3.67).toLocaleString()}</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<h3>Food and Groceries</h3>
<p>Monthly groceries for a household: AED {city.food.groceriesMonthly.min.toLocaleString()}-{city.food.groceriesMonthly.max.toLocaleString()} (~€{Math.round(city.food.groceriesMonthly.min * 0.25).toLocaleString()}-{Math.round(city.food.groceriesMonthly.max * 0.25).toLocaleString()}). Budget restaurant meal: AED {city.food.mealBudgetRestaurant.min}-{city.food.mealBudgetRestaurant.max} (~€{Math.round(city.food.mealBudgetRestaurant.min * 0.25)}-{Math.round(city.food.mealBudgetRestaurant.max * 0.25)}). Mid-range restaurant: AED {city.food.mealMidRange.min}-{city.food.mealMidRange.max} (~€{Math.round(city.food.mealMidRange.min * 0.25)}-{Math.round(city.food.mealMidRange.max * 0.25)}).</p>
<h3>Transport</h3>
<p>Metro monthly pass: AED {city.transport.metroMonthlyPass.amount || "N/A"} {city.transport.metroMonthlyPass.amount ? `(~€${Math.round(city.transport.metroMonthlyPass.amount * 0.25)})` : ""} {city.transport.metroMonthlyPass.note || ""}. Taxi per km: AED {city.transport.taxiPerKm.amount} (~€{(city.transport.taxiPerKm.amount * 0.25).toFixed(2)}). Petrol: AED {city.transport.gasolinePerLiter.amount}/liter (~€{(city.transport.gasolinePerLiter.amount * 0.25).toFixed(2)}). Car insurance: AED {city.transport.carInsuranceAnnual.min.toLocaleString()}-{city.transport.carInsuranceAnnual.max.toLocaleString()} (~€{Math.round(city.transport.carInsuranceAnnual.min * 0.25).toLocaleString()}-{Math.round(city.transport.carInsuranceAnnual.max * 0.25).toLocaleString()})/year.</p>
<h3>Healthcare</h3>
<p>GP visit: AED {city.healthcare.gpVisit.min}-{city.healthcare.gpVisit.max} (~€{Math.round(city.healthcare.gpVisit.min * 0.25)}-{Math.round(city.healthcare.gpVisit.max * 0.25)}). Specialist: AED {city.healthcare.specialistVisit.min}-{city.healthcare.specialistVisit.max} (~€{Math.round(city.healthcare.specialistVisit.min * 0.25)}-{Math.round(city.healthcare.specialistVisit.max * 0.25)}). Annual insurance: AED {city.healthcare.annualInsurance.min.toLocaleString()}-{city.healthcare.annualInsurance.max.toLocaleString()} (~€{Math.round(city.healthcare.annualInsurance.min * 0.25).toLocaleString()}-{Math.round(city.healthcare.annualInsurance.max * 0.25).toLocaleString()}) ({city.healthcare.annualInsurance.note || "employer-provided"}).</p>
<h3>Education</h3>
<p>International school: AED {city.education.internationalSchool.min.toLocaleString()}-{city.education.internationalSchool.max.toLocaleString()} (~€{Math.round(city.education.internationalSchool.min * 0.25).toLocaleString()}-{Math.round(city.education.internationalSchool.max * 0.25).toLocaleString()})/year. Nursery: AED {city.education.nursery.min.toLocaleString()}-{city.education.nursery.max.toLocaleString()} (~€{Math.round(city.education.nursery.min * 0.25).toLocaleString()}-{Math.round(city.education.nursery.max * 0.25).toLocaleString()})/year.</p>
<h3>Utilities</h3>
<p>Electricity and water: AED {city.utilities.monthly.min}-{city.utilities.monthly.max} (~€{Math.round(city.utilities.monthly.min * 0.25)}-{Math.round(city.utilities.monthly.max * 0.25)})/month. Internet: AED {city.utilities.internet.min}-{city.utilities.internet.max} (~€{Math.round(city.utilities.internet.min * 0.25)}-{Math.round(city.utilities.internet.max * 0.25)}). Mobile: AED {city.utilities.mobile.min}-{city.utilities.mobile.max} (~€{Math.round(city.utilities.mobile.min * 0.25)}-{Math.round(city.utilities.mobile.max * 0.25)}).</p>
</>
))}

<h2>Saving Money in the UAE</h2>
<p>Expats who budget carefully can save 25-40% of their income. Key strategies include choosing accommodation outside premium waterfront areas, shopping at budget-friendly supermarkets like Viva, LuLu, and Carrefour instead of organic or specialty stores, using the Dubai Metro for daily commuting (a Gold class pass costs AED 350 (~€88)/month compared to AED 2,000+ (~€500+) for parking plus fuel), and taking advantage of weekday restaurant deals and entertainment promotions. Many employers provide housing allowance separately, and some offer company accommodation that eliminates rent entirely. Cooking at home instead of dining out can save AED 1,500-2,500 (~€375-625) monthly. Building an emergency fund of 3-6 months' expenses is important because UAE employment law requires you to leave the country within 30 days of visa cancellation if you do not secure a new position.</p>

<FAQAccordion faqs={faqs} />
